title: Lady Eagles run their way to regionals
text:
Lady Eagles run their way to regionals Progress staff reports   
CARTHAGE - Rusk's Lady Eagles will be joining Henderson and Carthage at the upcoming Class 3A Region III Meet, to be staged in Huntsville on Oct. 26, after the trio of schools took the top-three spots at the District 19-3A Cross Country Meet late last week. 
The Lady Lions of Henderson scored 36 points to capture first place, ahead of Carthage (51) and Rusk (62). 
Domonique Uribe, posting a time of 13:58.6 came in sixth place in the individual standings to guide team Rusk. 
Zoe Ruben (14:04.3) ran seventh, while Claire Gresham (15:14.7) took 14th. 
Also scoring for Rusk in the team standings were Hannah Coleman (17th, 15:45.5) and Sammy Vargas (18th, 15:46.00). 
Breaking the tape at the finish line first was Caroline Rains from Henderson. Rains was timed in 12:49.6. 
Tatum came in fourth place by tallying 76 points, while Center did not field a complete unit.
